257 bool CheckImmRange(int immBits, int zeroBits, bool isSigned, 0
258 bool isRelocatable, bool Extendable) const { ----
259 if (Kind == Immediate) { 0
260 const MCExpr *myMCExpr = &HexagonMCInstrInfo::getExpr(*getImm()); 0
261 if (HexagonMCInstrInfo::mustExtend(*Imm.Val) && !Extendable) 0
262 return false; 0
263 int64_t Res; ----
264 if (myMCExpr->evaluateAsAbsolute(Res)) { 0
265 int bits = immBits + zeroBits; 0
266 // Field bit range is zerobits + bits ----
267 // zeroBits must be 0 ----
268 if (Res & ((1 << zeroBits) - 1)) 0
269 return false; 0
270 if (isSigned) { 0
271 if (Res < (1LL << (bits - 1)) && Res >= -(1LL << (bits - 1))) 0
272 return true; 0
273 } else { ----
274 if (bits == 64) 0
275 return true; 0
276 if (Res >= 0) 0
277 return ((uint64_t)Res < (uint64_t)(1ULL << bits)); 0
278 else { ----
279 const int64_t high_bit_set = 1ULL << 63; 0
280 const uint64_t mask = (high_bit_set >> (63 - bits)); 0
281 return (((uint64_t)Res & mask) == mask); 0
282 } ----
283 } ----
284 } else if (myMCExpr->getKind() == MCExpr::SymbolRef && isRelocatable) 0
285 return true; 0
286 else if (myMCExpr->getKind() == MCExpr::Binary || 0
287 myMCExpr->getKind() == MCExpr::Unary) 0
288 return true; 0
289 } ----
290 return false; 0
291 } ----

388 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!"); 0
389 HexagonMCExpr *Expr = ----
390 const_cast(cast(getImm())); 0
391 int64_t Value; ----
392 if (!Expr->evaluateAsAbsolute(Value)) { 0

395 } ----

397 HexagonMCExpr *NewExpr = HexagonMCExpr::create( 0

400 NewExpr->setSignMismatch(); 0

466 bool HexagonAsmParser::finishBundle(SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out) { 0
467 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Bundle:"); 0
468 LLVM_DEBUG(MCB.dump_pretty(dbgs())); 0
469 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "--\n"); 0
470 ----
471 MCB.setLoc(IDLoc); 0
472 ----
473 // Check the bundle for errors. ----
474 const MCRegisterInfo *RI = getContext().getRegisterInfo(); 0
475 MCSubtargetInfo const &STI = getSTI(); 0
476 ----
477 MCInst OrigBundle = MCB; 0
478 HexagonMCChecker Check(getContext(), MII, STI, MCB, *RI, true); 0
479 ----
480 bool CheckOk = HexagonMCInstrInfo::canonicalizePacket( 0
481 MII, STI, getContext(), MCB, &Check, true); 0
482 ----
483 if (CheckOk) { 0
484 if (HexagonMCInstrInfo::bundleSize(MCB) == 0) { 0
485 assert(!HexagonMCInstrInfo::isInnerLoop(MCB)); 0
486 assert(!HexagonMCInstrInfo::isOuterLoop(MCB)); 0
487 // Empty packets are valid yet aren't emitted ----
488 return false; 0
489 } ----
490 ----
491 assert(HexagonMCInstrInfo::isBundle(MCB)); 0
492 ----
493 Out.emitInstruction(MCB, STI); 0
494 } else ----
495 return true; // Error 0
496 ----
497 return false; // No error 0
498 } 0
499 ----
500 bool HexagonAsmParser::matchBundleOptions() { 0
501 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser(); 0
502 while (true) { ----
503 if (!Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Colon)) 0
504 return false; 0
505 Lex(); 0
506 char const *MemNoShuffMsg = 0
507 "invalid instruction packet: mem_noshuf specifier not " ----
508 "supported with this architecture"; ----
509 StringRef Option = Parser.getTok().getString(); 0
510 auto IDLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
511 if (Option.compare_insensitive("endloop01") == 0) { 0
512 HexagonMCInstrInfo::setInnerLoop(MCB); 0
513 HexagonMCInstrInfo::setOuterLoop(MCB); 0
514 } else if (Option.compare_insensitive("endloop0") == 0) { 0
515 HexagonMCInstrInfo::setInnerLoop(MCB); 0
516 } else if (Option.compare_insensitive("endloop1") == 0) { 0
517 HexagonMCInstrInfo::setOuterLoop(MCB); 0
518 } else if (Option.compare_insensitive("mem_noshuf") == 0) { 0
519 if (getSTI().hasFeature(Hexagon::FeatureMemNoShuf)) 0
520 HexagonMCInstrInfo::setMemReorderDisabled(MCB); 0
521 else ----
522 return getParser().Error(IDLoc, MemNoShuffMsg); 0
523 } else if (Option.compare_insensitive("mem_no_order") == 0) { 0
524 // Nothing. ----
525 } else ----
526 return getParser().Error(IDLoc, llvm::Twine("'") + Option + 0
527 "' is not a valid bundle option"); 0
528 Lex(); 0
529 } 0
530 } ----
531 ----
532 // For instruction aliases, immediates are generated rather than ----
533 // MCConstantExpr. Convert them for uniform MCExpr. ----
534 // Also check for signed/unsigned mismatches and warn ----
535 void HexagonAsmParser::canonicalizeImmediates(MCInst &MCI) { 0
536 MCInst NewInst; 0
537 NewInst.setOpcode(MCI.getOpcode()); 0
538 for (MCOperand &I : MCI) 0
539 if (I.isImm()) { 0
540 int64_t Value(I.getImm()); 0
541 NewInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(HexagonMCExpr::create( 0
542 MCConstantExpr::create(Value, getContext()), getContext()))); 0
543 } else { ----
544 if (I.isExpr() && cast(I.getExpr())->signMismatch() && 0
545 WarnSignedMismatch) 0
546 Warning(MCI.getLoc(), "Signed/Unsigned mismatch"); 0
547 NewInst.addOperand(I); 0
548 } ----
549 MCI = NewInst; 0
550 } 0
551 ----
552 bool HexagonAsmParser::matchOneInstruction(MCInst &MCI, SMLoc IDLoc, 0
553 OperandVector &InstOperands, ----
554 uint64_t &ErrorInfo, ----
555 bool MatchingInlineAsm) { ----
556 // Perform matching with tablegen asmmatcher generated function ----
557 int result = ----
558 MatchInstructionImpl(InstOperands, MCI, ErrorInfo, MatchingInlineAsm); 0
559 if (result == Match_Success) { 0
560 MCI.setLoc(IDLoc); 0
561 canonicalizeImmediates(MCI); 0
562 result = processInstruction(MCI, InstOperands, IDLoc); 0
563 ----
564 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Insn:"); 0
565 LLVM_DEBUG(MCI.dump_pretty(dbgs())); 0
566 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\n\n"); 0
567 ----
568 MCI.setLoc(IDLoc); 0
569 } ----
570 ----
571 // Create instruction operand for bundle instruction ----
572 // Break this into a separate function Code here is less readable ----
573 // Think about how to get an instruction error to report correctly. ----
574 // SMLoc will return the "{" ----
575 switch (result) { 0
576 default: 0
577 break; 0
578 case Match_Success: 0
579 return false; 0
580 case Match_MissingFeature: 0
581 return Error(IDLoc, "invalid instruction"); 0
582 case Match_MnemonicFail: 0
583 return Error(IDLoc, "unrecognized instruction"); 0
584 case Match_InvalidOperand: 0
585 [[fallthrough]]; ----
586 case Match_InvalidTiedOperand: ----
587 SMLoc ErrorLoc = IDLoc; 0
588 if (ErrorInfo != ~0U) { 0
589 if (ErrorInfo >= InstOperands.size()) 0
590 return Error(IDLoc, "too few operands for instruction"); 0
591 ----
592 ErrorLoc = (static_cast(InstOperands[ErrorInfo].get())) 0
593 ->getStartLoc(); 0
594 if (ErrorLoc == SMLoc()) 0
595 ErrorLoc = IDLoc; 0
596 } ----
597 return Error(ErrorLoc, "invalid operand for instruction"); 0
598 } ----
599 llvm_unreachable("Implement any new match types added!"); 0
600 } ----
601 ----
602 void HexagonAsmParser::eatToEndOfPacket() { 0
603 assert(InBrackets); 0
604 MCAsmLexer &Lexer = getLexer(); 0
605 while (!Lexer.is(AsmToken::RCurly)) 0
606 Lexer.Lex(); 0
607 Lexer.Lex(); 0
608 InBrackets = false; 0
609 } 0
610 ----
611 bool HexagonAsmParser::MatchAndEmitInstruction(SMLoc IDLoc, unsigned &Opcode, 0
612 OperandVector &Operands, ----
613 MCStreamer &Out, ----
614 uint64_t &ErrorInfo, ----
615 bool MatchingInlineAsm) { ----
616 if (!InBrackets) { 0
617 MCB.clear(); 0
618 MCB.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0)); 0
619 } ----
620 HexagonOperand &FirstOperand = static_cast(*Operands[0]); 0
621 if (FirstOperand.isToken() && FirstOperand.getToken() == "{") { 0
622 assert(Operands.size() == 1 && "Brackets should be by themselves"); 0
623 if (InBrackets) { 0
624 getParser().Error(IDLoc, "Already in a packet"); 0
625 InBrackets = false; 0
626 return true; 0
627 } ----
628 InBrackets = true; 0
629 return false; 0
630 } ----
631 if (FirstOperand.isToken() && FirstOperand.getToken() == "}") { 0
632 assert(Operands.size() == 1 && "Brackets should be by themselves"); 0
633 if (!InBrackets) { 0
634 getParser().Error(IDLoc, "Not in a packet"); 0
635 return true; 0
636 } ----
637 InBrackets = false; 0
638 if (matchBundleOptions()) 0
639 return true; 0
640 return finishBundle(IDLoc, Out); 0
641 } ----
642 MCInst *SubInst = getParser().getContext().createMCInst(); 0
643 if (matchOneInstruction(*SubInst, IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo, 0
644 MatchingInlineAsm)) { ----
645 if (InBrackets) 0
646 eatToEndOfPacket(); 0
647 return true; 0
648 } ----
649 HexagonMCInstrInfo::extendIfNeeded( 0
650 getParser().getContext(), MII, MCB, *SubInst); 0
651 MCB.addOperand(MCOperand::createInst(SubInst)); 0
652 if (!InBrackets) 0
653 return finishBundle(IDLoc, Out); 0
654 return false; 0
655 } ----
656 ----
657 /// ParseDirective parses the Hexagon specific directives ----
658 bool HexagonAsmParser::ParseDirective(AsmToken DirectiveID) { 0
659 StringRef IDVal = DirectiveID.getIdentifier(); 0
660 if (IDVal.lower() == ".falign") 0
661 return ParseDirectiveFalign(256, DirectiveID.getLoc()); 0
662 if ((IDVal.lower() == ".lcomm") || (IDVal.lower() == ".lcommon")) 0
663 return ParseDirectiveComm(true, DirectiveID.getLoc()); 0
664 if ((IDVal.lower() == ".comm") || (IDVal.lower() == ".common")) 0
665 return ParseDirectiveComm(false, DirectiveID.getLoc()); 0
666 if (IDVal.lower() == ".subsection") 0
667 return ParseDirectiveSubsection(DirectiveID.getLoc()); 0
668 ----
669 return true; 0
670 } ----
671 bool HexagonAsmParser::ParseDirectiveSubsection(SMLoc L) { 0
672 const MCExpr *Subsection = nullptr; 0
673 int64_t Res; ----
674 ----
675 assert((getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) && 0
676 "Invalid subsection directive"); ----
677 getParser().parseExpression(Subsection); 0
678 ----
679 if (!Subsection->evaluateAsAbsolute(Res)) 0
680 return Error(L, "Cannot evaluate subsection number"); 0
681 ----
682 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) 0
683 return TokError("unexpected token in directive"); 0
684 ----
685 // 0-8192 is the hard-coded range in MCObjectStreamper.cpp, this keeps the ----
686 // negative subsections together and in the same order but at the opposite ----
687 // end of the section. Only legacy hexagon-gcc created assembly code ----
688 // used negative subsections. ----
689 if ((Res < 0) && (Res > -8193)) 0
690 Subsection = HexagonMCExpr::create( 0
691 MCConstantExpr::create(8192 + Res, getContext()), getContext()); 0
692 ----
693 getStreamer().subSection(Subsection); 0
694 return false; 0
695 } ----
696 ----
697 /// ::= .falign [expression] ----
698 bool HexagonAsmParser::ParseDirectiveFalign(unsigned Size, SMLoc L) { 0
699 ----
700 int64_t MaxBytesToFill = 15; 0
701 ----
702 // if there is an argument ----
703 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) { 0
704 const MCExpr *Value; ----
705 SMLoc ExprLoc = L; 0
706 ----
707 // Make sure we have a number (false is returned if expression is a number) ----
708 if (!getParser().parseExpression(Value)) { 0
709 // Make sure this is a number that is in range ----
710 auto *MCE = cast(Value); 0
711 uint64_t IntValue = MCE->getValue(); 0
712 if (!isUIntN(Size, IntValue) && !isIntN(Size, IntValue)) 0
713 return Error(ExprLoc, "literal value out of range (256) for falign"); 0
714 MaxBytesToFill = IntValue; 0
715 Lex(); 0
716 } else { ----
717 return Error(ExprLoc, "not a valid expression for falign directive"); 0
718 } ----
719 } ----
720 ----
721 getTargetStreamer().emitFAlign(16, MaxBytesToFill); 0
722 Lex(); 0
723 ----
724 return false; 0
725 } ----
726 ----
727 // This is largely a copy of AsmParser's ParseDirectiveComm extended to ----
728 // accept a 3rd argument, AccessAlignment which indicates the smallest ----
729 // memory access made to the symbol, expressed in bytes. If no ----
730 // AccessAlignment is specified it defaults to the Alignment Value. ----
731 // Hexagon's .lcomm: ----
732 // .lcomm Symbol, Length, Alignment, AccessAlignment ----
733 bool HexagonAsmParser::ParseDirectiveComm(bool IsLocal, SMLoc Loc) { 0
734 // FIXME: need better way to detect if AsmStreamer (upstream removed ----
735 // getKind()) ----
736 if (getStreamer().hasRawTextSupport()) 0
737 return true; // Only object file output requires special treatment. 0
738 ----
739 StringRef Name; 0
740 if (getParser().parseIdentifier(Name)) 0
741 return TokError("expected identifier in directive"); 0
742 // Handle the identifier as the key symbol. ----
743 MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Name); 0
744 ----
745 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Comma)) 0
746 return TokError("unexpected token in directive"); 0
747 Lex(); 0
748 ----
749 int64_t Size; ----
750 SMLoc SizeLoc = getLexer().getLoc(); 0
751 if (getParser().parseAbsoluteExpression(Size)) 0
752 return true; 0
753 ----
754 int64_t ByteAlignment = 1; 0
755 SMLoc ByteAlignmentLoc; 0
756 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Comma)) { 0
757 Lex(); 0
758 ByteAlignmentLoc = getLexer().getLoc(); 0
759 if (getParser().parseAbsoluteExpression(ByteAlignment)) 0
760 return true; 0
761 if (!isPowerOf2_64(ByteAlignment)) 0
762 return Error(ByteAlignmentLoc, "alignment must be a power of 2"); 0
763 } ----
764 ----
765 int64_t AccessAlignment = 0; 0
766 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Comma)) { 0
767 // The optional access argument specifies the size of the smallest memory ----
768 // access to be made to the symbol, expressed in bytes. ----
769 SMLoc AccessAlignmentLoc; 0
770 Lex(); 0
771 AccessAlignmentLoc = getLexer().getLoc(); 0
772 if (getParser().parseAbsoluteExpression(AccessAlignment)) 0
773 return true; 0
774 ----
775 if (!isPowerOf2_64(AccessAlignment)) 0
776 return Error(AccessAlignmentLoc, "access alignment must be a power of 2"); 0
777 } ----
778 ----
779 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) 0
780 return TokError("unexpected token in '.comm' or '.lcomm' directive"); 0
781 ----
782 Lex(); 0
783 ----
784 // NOTE: a size of zero for a .comm should create a undefined symbol ----
785 // but a size of .lcomm creates a bss symbol of size zero. ----
786 if (Size < 0) 0
787 return Error(SizeLoc, "invalid '.comm' or '.lcomm' directive size, can't " 0
788 "be less than zero"); 0
789 ----
790 // NOTE: The alignment in the directive is a power of 2 value, the assembler ----
791 // may internally end up wanting an alignment in bytes. ----
792 // FIXME: Diagnose overflow. ----
793 if (ByteAlignment < 0) 0
794 return Error(ByteAlignmentLoc, "invalid '.comm' or '.lcomm' directive " 0
795 "alignment, can't be less than zero"); 0
796 ----
797 if (!Sym->isUndefined()) 0
798 return Error(Loc, "invalid symbol redefinition"); 0
799 ----
800 HexagonMCELFStreamer &HexagonELFStreamer = ----
801 static_cast(getStreamer()); 0
802 if (IsLocal) { 0
803 HexagonELFStreamer.HexagonMCEmitLocalCommonSymbol( 0
804 Sym, Size, Align(ByteAlignment), AccessAlignment); ----
805 return false; 0
806 } ----
807 ----
808 HexagonELFStreamer.HexagonMCEmitCommonSymbol(Sym, Size, Align(ByteAlignment), 0
809 AccessAlignment); ----
810 return false; 0
811 } ----
812 ----
813 // validate register against architecture ----
814 bool HexagonAsmParser::RegisterMatchesArch(unsigned MatchNum) const { 0
815 if (HexagonMCRegisterClasses[Hexagon::V62RegsRegClassID].contains(MatchNum)) 0
816 if (!getSTI().hasFeature(Hexagon::ArchV62)) 0
817 return false; 0
818 return true; 0
819 } ----

823 /// Force static initialization. ----
824 extern "C" LLVM_EXTERNAL_VISIBILITY void LLVMInitializeHexagonAsmParser() { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
825 RegisterMCAsmParser X(getTheHexagonTarget()); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
826 } 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
827 ----
828 #define GET_MATCHER_IMPLEMENTATION ----
829 #define GET_REGISTER_MATCHER ----
830 #include "HexagonGenAsmMatcher.inc" ----
831 ----
832 static bool previousEqual(OperandVector &Operands, size_t Index, 0
833 StringRef String) { ----
834 if (Index >= Operands.size()) 0
835 return false; 0
836 MCParsedAsmOperand &Operand = *Operands[Operands.size() - Index - 1]; 0
837 if (!Operand.isToken()) 0
838 return false; 0
839 return static_cast(Operand).getToken().equals_insensitive( 0
840 String); 0
841 } ----
842 ----
843 static bool previousIsLoop(OperandVector &Operands, size_t Index) { 0
844 return previousEqual(Operands, Index, "loop0") || 0
845 previousEqual(Operands, Index, "loop1") || 0
846 previousEqual(Operands, Index, "sp1loop0") || 0
847 previousEqual(Operands, Index, "sp2loop0") || 0
848 previousEqual(Operands, Index, "sp3loop0"); 0
849 } ----
850 ----
851 bool HexagonAsmParser::splitIdentifier(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
852 AsmToken const &Token = getParser().getTok(); 0
853 StringRef String = Token.getString(); 0
854 SMLoc Loc = Token.getLoc(); 0
855 Lex(); 0
856 do { ----
857 std::pair HeadTail = String.split('.'); 0
858 if (!HeadTail.first.empty()) 0
859 Operands.push_back( 0
860 HexagonOperand::CreateToken(getContext(), HeadTail.first, Loc)); 0
861 if (!HeadTail.second.empty()) 0
862 Operands.push_back(HexagonOperand::CreateToken( 0
863 getContext(), String.substr(HeadTail.first.size(), 1), Loc)); ----
864 String = HeadTail.second; 0
865 } while (!String.empty()); 0
866 return false; 0
867 } ----
868 ----
869 bool HexagonAsmParser::parseOperand(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
870 MCRegister Register; 0
871 SMLoc Begin; 0
872 SMLoc End; 0
873 MCAsmLexer &Lexer = getLexer(); 0
874 if (!parseRegister(Register, Begin, End)) { 0
875 if (!ErrorMissingParenthesis) 0
876 switch (Register) { 0
877 default: 0
878 break; 0
879 case Hexagon::P0: 0
880 case Hexagon::P1: ----
881 case Hexagon::P2: ----
882 case Hexagon::P3: ----
883 if (previousEqual(Operands, 0, "if")) { 0
884 if (WarnMissingParenthesis) 0
885 Warning(Begin, "Missing parenthesis around predicate register"); 0
886 static char const *LParen = "("; ----
887 static char const *RParen = ")"; ----
888 Operands.push_back( 0
889 HexagonOperand::CreateToken(getContext(), LParen, Begin)); 0
890 Operands.push_back( 0
891 HexagonOperand::CreateReg(getContext(), Register, Begin, End)); 0
892 const AsmToken &MaybeDotNew = Lexer.getTok(); 0
893 if (MaybeDotNew.is(AsmToken::TokenKind::Identifier) && 0
894 MaybeDotNew.getString().equals_insensitive(".new")) 0
895 splitIdentifier(Operands); 0
896 Operands.push_back( 0
897 HexagonOperand::CreateToken(getContext(), RParen, Begin)); 0
898 return false; 0
899 } ----
900 if (previousEqual(Operands, 0, "!") && 0
901 previousEqual(Operands, 1, "if")) { 0
902 if (WarnMissingParenthesis) 0
903 Warning(Begin, "Missing parenthesis around predicate register"); 0
904 static char const *LParen = "("; ----
905 static char const *RParen = ")"; ----
906 Operands.insert(Operands.end() - 1, HexagonOperand::CreateToken( 0
907 getContext(), LParen, Begin)); ----
908 Operands.push_back( 0
909 HexagonOperand::CreateReg(getContext(), Register, Begin, End)); 0
910 const AsmToken &MaybeDotNew = Lexer.getTok(); 0
911 if (MaybeDotNew.is(AsmToken::TokenKind::Identifier) && 0
912 MaybeDotNew.getString().equals_insensitive(".new")) 0
913 splitIdentifier(Operands); 0
914 Operands.push_back( 0
915 HexagonOperand::CreateToken(getContext(), RParen, Begin)); 0
916 return false; 0
917 } ----
918 break; 0
919 } ----
920 Operands.push_back( 0
921 HexagonOperand::CreateReg(getContext(), Register, Begin, End)); 0
922 return false; 0
923 } ----
924 return splitIdentifier(Operands); 0
925 } ----
926 ----
927 bool HexagonAsmParser::isLabel(AsmToken &Token) { 0
928 MCAsmLexer &Lexer = getLexer(); 0
929 AsmToken const &Second = Lexer.getTok(); 0
930 AsmToken Third = Lexer.peekTok(); 0
931 StringRef String = Token.getString(); 0
932 if (Token.is(AsmToken::TokenKind::LCurly) || 0
933 Token.is(AsmToken::TokenKind::RCurly)) 0
934 return false; 0
935 // special case for parsing vwhist256:sat ----
936 if (String.lower() == "vwhist256" && Second.is(AsmToken::Colon) && 0
937 Third.getString().lower() == "sat") 0
938 return false; 0
939 if (!Token.is(AsmToken::TokenKind::Identifier)) 0
940 return true; 0
941 if (!matchRegister(String.lower())) 0
942 return true; 0
943 assert(Second.is(AsmToken::Colon)); 0
944 StringRef Raw(String.data(), Third.getString().data() - String.data() + 0
945 Third.getString().size()); 0
946 std::string Collapsed = std::string(Raw); 0
947 llvm::erase_if(Collapsed, isSpace); 0
948 StringRef Whole = Collapsed; 0
949 std::pair DotSplit = Whole.split('.'); 0
950 if (!matchRegister(DotSplit.first.lower())) 0
951 return true; 0
952 return false; 0
953 } 0
954 ----
955 bool HexagonAsmParser::handleNoncontigiousRegister(bool Contigious, 0
956 SMLoc &Loc) { ----
957 if (!Contigious && ErrorNoncontigiousRegister) { 0
958 Error(Loc, "Register name is not contigious"); 0
959 return true; 0
960 } ----
961 if (!Contigious && WarnNoncontigiousRegister) 0
962 Warning(Loc, "Register name is not contigious"); 0
963 return false; 0
964 } ----
965 ----
966 bool HexagonAsmParser::parseRegister(MCRegister &RegNo, SMLoc &StartLoc, 0
967 SMLoc &EndLoc) { ----
968 return tryParseRegister(RegNo, StartLoc, EndLoc) != MatchOperand_Success; 0
969 } ----
970 ----
971 OperandMatchResultTy HexagonAsmParser::tryParseRegister(MCRegister &RegNo, 0
972 SMLoc &StartLoc, ----
973 SMLoc &EndLoc) { ----
974 MCAsmLexer &Lexer = getLexer(); 0
975 StartLoc = getLexer().getLoc(); 0
976 SmallVector Lookahead; 0
977 StringRef RawString(Lexer.getTok().getString().data(), 0); 0
978 bool Again = Lexer.is(AsmToken::Identifier); 0
979 bool NeededWorkaround = false; 0
980 while (Again) { 0
981 AsmToken const &Token = Lexer.getTok(); 0
982 RawString = StringRef(RawString.data(), Token.getString().data() - 0
983 RawString.data() + 0
984 Token.getString().size()); 0
985 Lookahead.push_back(Token); 0
986 Lexer.Lex(); 0
987 bool Contigious = Lexer.getTok().getString().data() == 0
988 Lookahead.back().getString().data() + 0
989 Lookahead.back().getString().size(); 0
990 bool Type = Lexer.is(AsmToken::Identifier) || Lexer.is(AsmToken::Dot) || 0
991 Lexer.is(AsmToken::Integer) || Lexer.is(AsmToken::Real) || 0
992 Lexer.is(AsmToken::Colon); 0
993 bool Workaround = ----
994 Lexer.is(AsmToken::Colon) || Lookahead.back().is(AsmToken::Colon); 0
995 Again = (Contigious && Type) || (Workaround && Type); 0
996 NeededWorkaround = NeededWorkaround || (Again && !(Contigious && Type)); 0
997 } ----
998 std::string Collapsed = std::string(RawString); 0
999 llvm::erase_if(Collapsed, isSpace); 0
1000 StringRef FullString = Collapsed; 0
1001 std::pair DotSplit = FullString.split('.'); 0
1002 unsigned DotReg = matchRegister(DotSplit.first.lower()); 0
1003 if (DotReg != Hexagon::NoRegister && RegisterMatchesArch(DotReg)) { 0
1004 if (DotSplit.second.empty()) { 0
1005 RegNo = DotReg; 0
1006 EndLoc = Lexer.getLoc(); 0
1007 if (handleNoncontigiousRegister(!NeededWorkaround, StartLoc)) 0
1008 return MatchOperand_NoMatch; 0
1009 return MatchOperand_Success; 0
1010 } else { ----
1011 RegNo = DotReg; 0
1012 size_t First = RawString.find('.'); 0
1013 StringRef DotString (RawString.data() + First, RawString.size() - First); 0
1014 Lexer.UnLex(AsmToken(AsmToken::Identifier, DotString)); 0
1015 EndLoc = Lexer.getLoc(); 0
1016 if (handleNoncontigiousRegister(!NeededWorkaround, StartLoc)) 0
1017 return MatchOperand_NoMatch; 0
1018 return MatchOperand_Success; 0
1019 } ----
1020 } ----
1021 std::pair ColonSplit = StringRef(FullString).split(':'); 0
1022 unsigned ColonReg = matchRegister(ColonSplit.first.lower()); 0
1023 if (ColonReg != Hexagon::NoRegister && RegisterMatchesArch(DotReg)) { 0
1024 do { ----
1025 Lexer.UnLex(Lookahead.pop_back_val()); 0
1026 } while (!Lookahead.empty() && !Lexer.is(AsmToken::Colon)); 0
1027 RegNo = ColonReg; 0
1028 EndLoc = Lexer.getLoc(); 0
1029 if (handleNoncontigiousRegister(!NeededWorkaround, StartLoc)) 0
1030 return MatchOperand_NoMatch; 0
1031 return MatchOperand_Success; 0
1032 } ----
1033 while (!Lookahead.empty()) { 0
1034 Lexer.UnLex(Lookahead.pop_back_val()); 0
1035 } ----
1036 return MatchOperand_NoMatch; 0
1037 } 0
1038 ----
1039 bool HexagonAsmParser::implicitExpressionLocation(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
1040 if (previousEqual(Operands, 0, "call")) 0
1041 return true; 0
1042 if (previousEqual(Operands, 0, "jump")) 0
1043 if (!getLexer().getTok().is(AsmToken::Colon)) 0
1044 return true; 0
1045 if (previousEqual(Operands, 0, "(") && previousIsLoop(Operands, 1)) 0
1046 return true; 0
1047 if (previousEqual(Operands, 1, ":") && previousEqual(Operands, 2, "jump") && 0
1048 (previousEqual(Operands, 0, "nt") || previousEqual(Operands, 0, "t"))) 0
1049 return true; 0
1050 return false; 0
1051 } ----
1052 ----
1053 bool HexagonAsmParser::parseExpression(MCExpr const *&Expr) { 0
1054 SmallVector Tokens; 0
1055 MCAsmLexer &Lexer = getLexer(); 0
1056 bool Done = false; 0
1057 static char const *Comma = ","; ----
1058 do { ----
1059 Tokens.emplace_back(Lexer.getTok()); 0
1060 Lex(); 0
1061 switch (Tokens.back().getKind()) { 0
1062 case AsmToken::TokenKind::Hash: 0
1063 if (Tokens.size() > 1) 0
1064 if ((Tokens.end() - 2)->getKind() == AsmToken::TokenKind::Plus) { 0
1065 Tokens.insert(Tokens.end() - 2, 0
1066 AsmToken(AsmToken::TokenKind::Comma, Comma)); 0
1067 Done = true; 0
1068 } ----
1069 break; 0
1070 case AsmToken::TokenKind::RCurly: 0
1071 case AsmToken::TokenKind::EndOfStatement: ----
1072 case AsmToken::TokenKind::Eof: ----
1073 Done = true; 0
1074 break; 0
1075 default: 0
1076 break; 0
1077 } ----
1078 } while (!Done); 0
1079 while (!Tokens.empty()) { 0
1080 Lexer.UnLex(Tokens.back()); 0
1081 Tokens.pop_back(); 0
1082 } ----
1083 SMLoc Loc = Lexer.getLoc(); 0
1084 return getParser().parseExpression(Expr, Loc); 0
1085 } 0
1086 ----
1087 bool HexagonAsmParser::parseExpressionOrOperand(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
1088 if (implicitExpressionLocation(Operands)) { 0
1089 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser(); 0
1090 SMLoc Loc = Parser.getLexer().getLoc(); 0
1091 MCExpr const *Expr = nullptr; 0
1092 bool Error = parseExpression(Expr); 0
1093 Expr = HexagonMCExpr::create(Expr, getContext()); 0
1094 if (!Error) 0
1095 Operands.push_back( 0
1096 HexagonOperand::CreateImm(getContext(), Expr, Loc, Loc)); 0
1097 return Error; 0
1098 } ----
1099 return parseOperand(Operands); 0
1100 } ----
1101 ----
1102 /// Parse an instruction. ----
1103 bool HexagonAsmParser::parseInstruction(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
1104 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser(); 0
1105 MCAsmLexer &Lexer = getLexer(); 0
1106 while (true) { ----
1107 AsmToken const &Token = Parser.getTok(); 0
1108 switch (Token.getKind()) { 0
1109 case AsmToken::Eof: 0
1110 case AsmToken::EndOfStatement: { ----
1111 Lex(); 0
1112 return false; 0
1113 } ----
1114 case AsmToken::LCurly: { 0
1115 if (!Operands.empty()) 0
1116 return true; 0
1117 Operands.push_back(HexagonOperand::CreateToken( 0
1118 getContext(), Token.getString(), Token.getLoc())); ----
1119 Lex(); 0
1120 return false; 0
1121 } ----
1122 case AsmToken::RCurly: { 0
1123 if (Operands.empty()) { 0
1124 Operands.push_back(HexagonOperand::CreateToken( 0
1125 getContext(), Token.getString(), Token.getLoc())); ----
1126 Lex(); 0
1127 } ----
1128 return false; 0
1129 } ----
1130 case AsmToken::Comma: { 0
1131 Lex(); 0
1132 continue; 0
1133 } ----
1134 case AsmToken::EqualEqual: 0
1135 case AsmToken::ExclaimEqual: ----
1136 case AsmToken::GreaterEqual: ----
1137 case AsmToken::GreaterGreater: ----
1138 case AsmToken::LessEqual: ----
1139 case AsmToken::LessLess: { ----
1140 Operands.push_back(HexagonOperand::CreateToken( 0
1141 getContext(), Token.getString().substr(0, 1), Token.getLoc())); 0
1142 Operands.push_back(HexagonOperand::CreateToken( 0
1143 getContext(), Token.getString().substr(1, 1), Token.getLoc())); 0
1144 Lex(); 0
1145 continue; 0
1146 } ----
1147 case AsmToken::Hash: { 0
1148 bool MustNotExtend = false; 0
1149 bool ImplicitExpression = implicitExpressionLocation(Operands); 0
1150 SMLoc ExprLoc = Lexer.getLoc(); 0
1151 if (!ImplicitExpression) 0
1152 Operands.push_back(HexagonOperand::CreateToken( 0
1153 getContext(), Token.getString(), Token.getLoc())); ----
1154 Lex(); 0
1155 bool MustExtend = false; 0
1156 bool HiOnly = false; 0
1157 bool LoOnly = false; 0
1158 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Hash)) { 0
1159 Lex(); 0
1160 MustExtend = true; 0
1161 } else if (ImplicitExpression) 0
1162 MustNotExtend = true; 0
1163 AsmToken const &Token = Parser.getTok(); 0
1164 if (Token.is(AsmToken::Identifier)) { 0
1165 StringRef String = Token.getString(); 0
1166 if (String.lower() == "hi") { 0
1167 HiOnly = true; 0
1168 } else if (String.lower() == "lo") { 0
1169 LoOnly = true; 0
1170 } ----
1171 if (HiOnly || LoOnly) { 0
1172 AsmToken LParen = Lexer.peekTok(); 0
1173 if (!LParen.is(AsmToken::LParen)) { 0
1174 HiOnly = false; 0
1175 LoOnly = false; 0
1176 } else { ----
1177 Lex(); 0
1178 } ----
1179 } 0
1180 } ----
1181 MCExpr const *Expr = nullptr; 0
1182 if (parseExpression(Expr)) 0
1183 return true; 0
1184 int64_t Value; ----
1185 MCContext &Context = Parser.getContext(); 0
1186 assert(Expr != nullptr); 0
1187 if (Expr->evaluateAsAbsolute(Value)) { 0
1188 if (HiOnly) 0
1189 Expr = MCBinaryExpr::createLShr( 0
1190 Expr, MCConstantExpr::create(16, Context), Context); 0
1191 if (HiOnly || LoOnly) 0
1192 Expr = MCBinaryExpr::createAnd( 0
1193 Expr, MCConstantExpr::create(0xffff, Context), Context); 0
1194 } else { ----
1195 MCValue Value; 0
1196 if (Expr->evaluateAsRelocatable(Value, nullptr, nullptr)) { 0
1197 if (!Value.isAbsolute()) { 0
1198 switch (Value.getAccessVariant()) { 0
1199 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind::VK_TPREL: 0
1200 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind::VK_DTPREL: ----
1201 // Don't lazy extend these expression variants ----
1202 MustNotExtend = !MustExtend; 0
1203 break; 0
1204 default: 0
1205 break; 0
1206 } ----
1207 } ----
1208 } ----
1209 } ----
1210 Expr = HexagonMCExpr::create(Expr, Context); 0
1211 HexagonMCInstrInfo::setMustNotExtend(*Expr, MustNotExtend); 0
1212 HexagonMCInstrInfo::setMustExtend(*Expr, MustExtend); 0
1213 std::unique_ptr Operand = ----
1214 HexagonOperand::CreateImm(getContext(), Expr, ExprLoc, ExprLoc); 0
1215 Operands.push_back(std::move(Operand)); 0
1216 continue; 0
1217 } ----
1218 default: 0
1219 break; 0
1220 } 0
1221 if (parseExpressionOrOperand(Operands)) 0
1222 return true; 0
1223 } 0
1224 } ----
1225 ----
1226 bool HexagonAsmParser::ParseInstruction(ParseInstructionInfo &Info, 0
1227 StringRef Name, AsmToken ID, ----
1228 OperandVector &Operands) { ----
1229 getLexer().UnLex(ID); 0
1230 return parseInstruction(Operands); 0
1231 } ----
1232 ----
1233 static MCInst makeCombineInst(int opCode, MCOperand &Rdd, MCOperand &MO1, 0
1234 MCOperand &MO2) { ----
1235 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1236 TmpInst.setOpcode(opCode); 0
1237 TmpInst.addOperand(Rdd); 0
1238 TmpInst.addOperand(MO1); 0
1239 TmpInst.addOperand(MO2); 0
1240 ----
1241 return TmpInst; 0
1242 } ----
1243 ----
1244 // Define this matcher function after the auto-generated include so we ----
1245 // have the match class enum definitions. ----
1246 unsigned HexagonAsmParser::validateTargetOperandClass(MCParsedAsmOperand &AsmOp, 0
1247 unsigned Kind) { ----
1248 HexagonOperand *Op = static_cast(&AsmOp); 0
1249 ----
1250 switch (Kind) { 0
1251 case MCK_0: { 0
1252 int64_t Value; ----
1253 return Op->isImm() && Op->Imm.Val->evaluateAsAbsolute(Value) && Value == 0 0
1254 ? Match_Success 0
1255 : Match_InvalidOperand; 0
1256 } ----
1257 case MCK_1: { 0
1258 int64_t Value; ----
1259 return Op->isImm() && Op->Imm.Val->evaluateAsAbsolute(Value) && Value == 1 0
1260 ? Match_Success 0
1261 : Match_InvalidOperand; 0
1262 } ----
1263 } ----
1264 if (Op->Kind == HexagonOperand::Token && Kind != InvalidMatchClass) { 0
1265 StringRef myStringRef = StringRef(Op->Tok.Data, Op->Tok.Length); 0
1266 if (matchTokenString(myStringRef.lower()) == (MatchClassKind)Kind) 0
1267 return Match_Success; 0
1268 if (matchTokenString(myStringRef.upper()) == (MatchClassKind)Kind) 0
1269 return Match_Success; 0
1270 } ----
1271 ----
1272 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Unmatched Operand:"); 0
1273 LLVM_DEBUG(Op->dump()); 0
1274 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\n"); 0
1275 ----
1276 return Match_InvalidOperand; 0
1277 } ----
1278 ----
1279 // FIXME: Calls to OutOfRange shoudl propagate failure up to parseStatement. ----
1280 bool HexagonAsmParser::OutOfRange(SMLoc IDLoc, long long Val, long long Max) { 0
1281 std::string errStr; 0
1282 raw_string_ostream ES(errStr); 0
1283 ES << "value " << Val << "(" << format_hex(Val, 0) << ") out of range: "; 0
1284 if (Max >= 0) 0
1285 ES << "0-" << Max; 0
1286 else ----
1287 ES << Max << "-" << (-Max - 1); 0
1288 return Parser.printError(IDLoc, ES.str()); 0
1289 } 0
1290 ----
1291 int HexagonAsmParser::processInstruction(MCInst &Inst, 0
1292 OperandVector const &Operands, ----
1293 SMLoc IDLoc) { ----
1294 MCContext &Context = getParser().getContext(); 0
1295 const MCRegisterInfo *RI = getContext().getRegisterInfo(); 0
1296 const std::string r = "r"; 0
1297 const std::string v = "v"; 0
1298 const std::string Colon = ":"; 0
1299 using RegPairVals = std::pair; ----
1300 auto GetRegPair = [this, r](RegPairVals RegPair) { 0
1301 const std::string R1 = r + utostr(RegPair.first); 0
1302 const std::string R2 = r + utostr(RegPair.second); 0
1303 ----
1304 return std::make_pair(matchRegister(R1), matchRegister(R2)); 0
1305 }; 0
1306 auto GetScalarRegs = [RI, GetRegPair](unsigned RegPair) { 0
1307 const unsigned Lower = RI->getEncodingValue(RegPair); 0
1308 const RegPairVals RegPair_ = std::make_pair(Lower + 1, Lower); 0
1309 ----
1310 return GetRegPair(RegPair_); 0
1311 }; 0
1312 auto GetVecRegs = [GetRegPair](unsigned VecRegPair) { 0
1313 const RegPairVals RegPair = ----
1314 HexagonMCInstrInfo::GetVecRegPairIndices(VecRegPair); 0
1315 ----
1316 return GetRegPair(RegPair); 0
1317 }; 0
1318 ----
1319 bool is32bit = false; // used to distinguish between CONST32 and CONST64 0
1320 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) { 0
1321 default: 0
1322 if (HexagonMCInstrInfo::getDesc(MII, Inst).isPseudo()) { 0
1323 SMDiagnostic Diag = getSourceManager().GetMessage( 0
1324 IDLoc, SourceMgr::DK_Error, ----
1325 "Found pseudo instruction with no expansion"); 0
1326 Diag.print("", errs()); 0
1327 report_fatal_error("Invalid pseudo instruction"); 0
1328 } ----
1329 break; 0
1330 ----
1331 case Hexagon::J2_trap1: 0
1332 if (!getSTI().hasFeature(Hexagon::ArchV65)) { 0
1333 MCOperand &Rx = Inst.getOperand(0); 0
1334 MCOperand &Ry = Inst.getOperand(1); 0
1335 if (Rx.getReg() != Hexagon::R0 || Ry.getReg() != Hexagon::R0) { 0
1336 Error(IDLoc, "trap1 can only have register r0 as operand"); 0
1337 return Match_InvalidOperand; 0
1338 } ----
1339 } ----
1340 break; 0
1341 ----
1342 case Hexagon::A2_iconst: { 0
1343 Inst.setOpcode(Hexagon::A2_addi); 0
1344 MCOperand Reg = Inst.getOperand(0); 0
1345 MCOperand S27 = Inst.getOperand(1); 0
1346 HexagonMCInstrInfo::setMustNotExtend(*S27.getExpr()); 0
1347 HexagonMCInstrInfo::setS27_2_reloc(*S27.getExpr()); 0
1348 Inst.clear(); 0
1349 Inst.addOperand(Reg); 0
1350 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Hexagon::R0)); 0
1351 Inst.addOperand(S27); 0
1352 break; 0
1353 } ----
1354 case Hexagon::M4_mpyrr_addr: 0
1355 case Hexagon::S4_addi_asl_ri: ----
1356 case Hexagon::S4_addi_lsr_ri: ----
1357 case Hexagon::S4_andi_asl_ri: ----
1358 case Hexagon::S4_andi_lsr_ri: ----
1359 case Hexagon::S4_ori_asl_ri: ----
1360 case Hexagon::S4_ori_lsr_ri: ----
1361 case Hexagon::S4_or_andix: ----
1362 case Hexagon::S4_subi_asl_ri: ----
1363 case Hexagon::S4_subi_lsr_ri: { ----
1364 MCOperand &Ry = Inst.getOperand(0); 0
1365 MCOperand &src = Inst.getOperand(2); 0
1366 if (RI->getEncodingValue(Ry.getReg()) != RI->getEncodingValue(src.getReg())) 0
1367 return Match_InvalidOperand; 0
1368 break; 0
1369 } ----
1370 ----
1371 case Hexagon::C2_cmpgei: { 0
1372 MCOperand &MO = Inst.getOperand(2); 0
1373 MO.setExpr(HexagonMCExpr::create( 0
1374 MCBinaryExpr::createSub(MO.getExpr(), 0
1375 MCConstantExpr::create(1, Context), Context), 0
1376 Context)); ----
1377 Inst.setOpcode(Hexagon::C2_cmpgti); 0
1378 break; 0
1379 } ----
1380 ----
1381 case Hexagon::C2_cmpgeui: { 0
1382 MCOperand &MO = Inst.getOperand(2); 0
1383 int64_t Value; ----
1384 bool Success = MO.getExpr()->evaluateAsAbsolute(Value); 0
1385 (void)Success; ----
1386 assert(Success && "Assured by matcher"); 0
1387 if (Value == 0) { 0
1388 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1389 MCOperand &Pd = Inst.getOperand(0); 0
1390 MCOperand &Rt = Inst.getOperand(1); 0
1391 TmpInst.setOpcode(Hexagon::C2_cmpeq); 0
1392 TmpInst.addOperand(Pd); 0
1393 TmpInst.addOperand(Rt); 0
1394 TmpInst.addOperand(Rt); 0
1395 Inst = TmpInst; 0
1396 } else { 0
1397 MO.setExpr(HexagonMCExpr::create( 0
1398 MCBinaryExpr::createSub(MO.getExpr(), 0
1399 MCConstantExpr::create(1, Context), Context), 0
1400 Context)); ----
1401 Inst.setOpcode(Hexagon::C2_cmpgtui); 0
1402 } ----
1403 break; 0
1404 } ----
1405 ----
1406 // Translate a "$Rdd = $Rss" to "$Rdd = combine($Rs, $Rt)" ----
1407 case Hexagon::A2_tfrp: { 0
1408 MCOperand &MO = Inst.getOperand(1); 0
1409 const std::pair RegPair = GetScalarRegs(MO.getReg()); 0
1410 MO.setReg(RegPair.first); 0
1411 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(RegPair.second)); 0
1412 Inst.setOpcode(Hexagon::A2_combinew); 0
1413 break; 0
1414 } ----
1415 ----
1416 case Hexagon::A2_tfrpt: 0
1417 case Hexagon::A2_tfrpf: { ----
1418 MCOperand &MO = Inst.getOperand(2); 0
1419 const std::pair RegPair = GetScalarRegs(MO.getReg()); 0
1420 MO.setReg(RegPair.first); 0
1421 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(RegPair.second)); 0
1422 Inst.setOpcode((Inst.getOpcode() == Hexagon::A2_tfrpt) 0
1423 ? Hexagon::C2_ccombinewt ----
1424 : Hexagon::C2_ccombinewf); ----
1425 break; 0
1426 } ----
1427 case Hexagon::A2_tfrptnew: 0
1428 case Hexagon::A2_tfrpfnew: { ----
1429 MCOperand &MO = Inst.getOperand(2); 0
1430 const std::pair RegPair = GetScalarRegs(MO.getReg()); 0
1431 MO.setReg(RegPair.first); 0
1432 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(RegPair.second)); 0
1433 Inst.setOpcode((Inst.getOpcode() == Hexagon::A2_tfrptnew) 0
1434 ? Hexagon::C2_ccombinewnewt ----
1435 : Hexagon::C2_ccombinewnewf); ----
1436 break; 0
1437 } ----
1438 ----
1439 // Translate a "$Vdd = $Vss" to "$Vdd = vcombine($Vs, $Vt)" ----
1440 case Hexagon::V6_vassignp: { 0
1441 MCOperand &MO = Inst.getOperand(1); 0
1442 const std::pair RegPair = GetVecRegs(MO.getReg()); 0
1443 MO.setReg(RegPair.first); 0
1444 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(RegPair.second)); 0
1445 Inst.setOpcode(Hexagon::V6_vcombine); 0
1446 break; 0
1447 } ----
1448 ----
1449 // Translate a "$Rx = CONST32(#imm)" to "$Rx = memw(gp+#LABEL) " ----
1450 case Hexagon::CONST32: 0
1451 is32bit = true; 0
1452 [[fallthrough]]; ----
1453 // Translate a "$Rx:y = CONST64(#imm)" to "$Rx:y = memd(gp+#LABEL) " ----
1454 case Hexagon::CONST64: 0
1455 // FIXME: need better way to detect AsmStreamer (upstream removed getKind()) ----
1456 if (!Parser.getStreamer().hasRawTextSupport()) { 0
1457 MCELFStreamer *MES = static_cast(&Parser.getStreamer()); 0
1458 MCOperand &MO_1 = Inst.getOperand(1); 0
1459 MCOperand &MO_0 = Inst.getOperand(0); 0
1460 ----
1461 // push section onto section stack ----
1462 MES->pushSection(); 0
1463 ----
1464 std::string myCharStr; 0
1465 MCSectionELF *mySection; ----
1466 ----
1467 // check if this as an immediate or a symbol ----
1468 int64_t Value; ----
1469 bool Absolute = MO_1.getExpr()->evaluateAsAbsolute(Value); 0
1470 if (Absolute) { 0
1471 // Create a new section - one for each constant ----
1472 // Some or all of the zeros are replaced with the given immediate. ----
1473 if (is32bit) { 0
1474 std::string myImmStr = utohexstr(static_cast(Value)); 0
1475 myCharStr = StringRef(".gnu.linkonce.l4.CONST_00000000") 0
1476 .drop_back(myImmStr.size()) 0
1477 .str() + 0
1478 myImmStr; 0
1479 } else { 0
1480 std::string myImmStr = utohexstr(Value); 0
1481 myCharStr = StringRef(".gnu.linkonce.l8.CONST_0000000000000000") 0
1482 .drop_back(myImmStr.size()) 0
1483 .str() + 0
1484 myImmStr; 0
1485 } 0
1486 ----
1487 mySection = getContext().getELFSection(myCharStr, ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, 0
1488 ELF::SHF_ALLOC | ELF::SHF_WRITE); ----
1489 } else if (MO_1.isExpr()) { 0
1490 // .lita - for expressions ----
1491 myCharStr = ".lita"; 0
1492 mySection = getContext().getELFSection(myCharStr, ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, 0
1493 ELF::SHF_ALLOC | ELF::SHF_WRITE); ----
1494 } else ----
1495 llvm_unreachable("unexpected type of machine operand!"); 0
1496 ----
1497 MES->switchSection(mySection); 0
1498 unsigned byteSize = is32bit ? 4 : 8; 0
1499 getStreamer().emitCodeAlignment(Align(byteSize), &getSTI(), byteSize); 0
1500 ----
1501 MCSymbol *Sym; ----
1502 ----
1503 // for symbols, get rid of prepended ".gnu.linkonce.lx." ----
1504 ----
1505 // emit symbol if needed ----
1506 if (Absolute) { 0
1507 Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(StringRef(myCharStr.c_str() + 16)); 0
1508 if (Sym->isUndefined()) { 0
1509 getStreamer().emitLabel(Sym); 0
1510 getStreamer().emitSymbolAttribute(Sym, MCSA_Global); 0
1511 getStreamer().emitIntValue(Value, byteSize); 0
1512 } ----
1513 } else if (MO_1.isExpr()) { 0
1514 const char *StringStart = nullptr; 0
1515 const char *StringEnd = nullptr; 0
1516 if (*Operands[4]->getStartLoc().getPointer() == '#') { 0
1517 StringStart = Operands[5]->getStartLoc().getPointer(); 0
1518 StringEnd = Operands[6]->getStartLoc().getPointer(); 0
1519 } else { // no pound ----
1520 StringStart = Operands[4]->getStartLoc().getPointer(); 0
1521 StringEnd = Operands[5]->getStartLoc().getPointer(); 0
1522 } ----
1523 ----
1524 unsigned size = StringEnd - StringStart; 0
1525 std::string DotConst = ".CONST_"; 0
1526 Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(DotConst + 0
1527 StringRef(StringStart, size)); 0
1528 ----
1529 if (Sym->isUndefined()) { 0
1530 // case where symbol is not yet defined: emit symbol ----
1531 getStreamer().emitLabel(Sym); 0
1532 getStreamer().emitSymbolAttribute(Sym, MCSA_Local); 0
1533 getStreamer().emitValue(MO_1.getExpr(), 4); 0
1534 } ----
1535 } else 0
1536 llvm_unreachable("unexpected type of machine operand!"); 0
1537 ----
1538 MES->popSection(); 0
1539 ----
1540 if (Sym) { 0
1541 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1542 if (is32bit) // 32 bit 0
1543 TmpInst.setOpcode(Hexagon::L2_loadrigp); 0
1544 else // 64 bit ----
1545 TmpInst.setOpcode(Hexagon::L2_loadrdgp); 0
1546 ----
1547 TmpInst.addOperand(MO_0); 0
1548 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(HexagonMCExpr::create( 0
1549 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, getContext()), getContext()))); 0
1550 Inst = TmpInst; 0
1551 } 0
1552 } 0
1553 break; 0
1554 ----
1555 // Translate a "$Rdd = #-imm" to "$Rdd = combine(#[-1,0], #-imm)" ----
1556 case Hexagon::A2_tfrpi: { 0
1557 MCOperand &Rdd = Inst.getOperand(0); 0
1558 MCOperand &MO = Inst.getOperand(1); 0
1559 int64_t Value; ----
1560 int sVal = (MO.getExpr()->evaluateAsAbsolute(Value) && Value < 0) ? -1 : 0; 0
1561 MCOperand imm(MCOperand::createExpr( 0
1562 HexagonMCExpr::create(MCConstantExpr::create(sVal, Context), Context))); 0
1563 Inst = makeCombineInst(Hexagon::A2_combineii, Rdd, imm, MO); 0
1564 break; 0
1565 } ----
1566 ----
1567 // Translate a "$Rdd = [#]#imm" to "$Rdd = combine(#, [#]#imm)" ----
1568 case Hexagon::TFRI64_V4: { 0
1569 MCOperand &Rdd = Inst.getOperand(0); 0
1570 MCOperand &MO = Inst.getOperand(1); 0
1571 int64_t Value; ----
1572 if (MO.getExpr()->evaluateAsAbsolute(Value)) { 0
1573 int s8 = Hi_32(Value); 0
1574 if (!isInt<8>(s8)) 0
1575 OutOfRange(IDLoc, s8, -128); 0
1576 MCOperand imm(MCOperand::createExpr(HexagonMCExpr::create( 0
1577 MCConstantExpr::create(s8, Context), Context))); // upper 32 0
1578 auto Expr = HexagonMCExpr::create( 0

1580 HexagonMCInstrInfo::setMustExtend( 0
1581 *Expr, HexagonMCInstrInfo::mustExtend(*MO.getExpr())); 0
1582 MCOperand imm2(MCOperand::createExpr(Expr)); // lower 32 0
1583 Inst = makeCombineInst(Hexagon::A4_combineii, Rdd, imm, imm2); 0
1584 } else { ----
1585 MCOperand imm(MCOperand::createExpr(HexagonMCExpr::create( 0
1586 MCConstantExpr::create(0, Context), Context))); // upper 32 0
1587 Inst = makeCombineInst(Hexagon::A4_combineii, Rdd, imm, MO); 0
1588 } ----
1589 break; 0
1590 } ----
1591 ----
1592 // Handle $Rdd = combine(##imm, #imm)" ----
1593 case Hexagon::TFRI64_V2_ext: { 0
1594 MCOperand &Rdd = Inst.getOperand(0); 0
1595 MCOperand &MO1 = Inst.getOperand(1); 0

1598 if (MO2.getExpr()->evaluateAsAbsolute(Value)) { 0
1599 int s8 = Value; 0
1600 if (s8 < -128 || s8 > 127) 0
1601 OutOfRange(IDLoc, s8, -128); 0
1602 } ----

1604 break; 0
1605 } ----
1606 ----
1607 // Handle $Rdd = combine(#imm, ##imm)" ----
1608 case Hexagon::A4_combineii: { 0
1609 MCOperand &Rdd = Inst.getOperand(0); 0
1610 MCOperand &MO1 = Inst.getOperand(1); 0
1611 int64_t Value; ----
1612 if (MO1.getExpr()->evaluateAsAbsolute(Value)) { 0
1613 int s8 = Value; 0
1614 if (s8 < -128 || s8 > 127) 0
1615 OutOfRange(IDLoc, s8, -128); 0
1616 } ----

1618 Inst = makeCombineInst(Hexagon::A4_combineii, Rdd, MO1, MO2); 0
1619 break; 0
1620 } ----
1621 ----
1622 case Hexagon::S2_tableidxb_goodsyntax: 0
1623 Inst.setOpcode(Hexagon::S2_tableidxb); 0

1697 if (!Absolute) 0
1698 return Match_InvalidOperand; 0
1699 if (!HexagonMCInstrInfo::mustExtend(Expr) && 0
1700 ((Value <= -256) || Value >= 256)) 0
1701 return Match_InvalidOperand; 0
1702 if (Value < 0 && Value > -256) { 0

1704 MCConstantExpr::create(Value * -1, Context), Context)); 0

1706 } else ----
1707 TmpInst.setOpcode(Hexagon::M2_mpysip); 0
1708 TmpInst.addOperand(Rd); 0

1712 break; 0
1713 } 0
1714 ----
1715 case Hexagon::S2_asr_i_r_rnd_goodsyntax: { 0
1716 MCOperand &Imm = Inst.getOperand(2); 0
1717 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1718 int64_t Value; ----
1719 bool Absolute = Imm.getExpr()->evaluateAsAbsolute(Value); 0
1720 if (!Absolute) 0
1721 return Match_InvalidOperand; 0
1722 if (Value == 0) { // convert to $Rd = $Rs 0
1723 TmpInst.setOpcode(Hexagon::A2_tfr); 0
1724 MCOperand &Rd = Inst.getOperand(0); 0

257 bool CheckImmRange(int immBits, int zeroBits, bool isSigned, 257 bool CheckImmRange(int immBits, int zeroBits, bool isSigned,
258 bool isRelocatable, bool Extendable) const { 258 bool isRelocatable, bool Extendable) const {
259 if (Kind == Immediate) { 259 if (Kind == Immediate) {
260 const MCExpr *myMCExpr = &HexagonMCInstrInfo::getExpr(*getImm()); 260 const MCExpr *myMCExpr = &HexagonMCInstrInfo::getExpr(*getImm());
261 if (HexagonMCInstrInfo::mustExtend(*Imm.Val) && !Extendable) 261 if (HexagonMCInstrInfo::mustExtend(*Imm.Val) && !Extendable)
262 return false; 262 return false;
263 int64_t Res; 263 int64_t Res;
264 if (myMCExpr->evaluateAsAbsolute(Res)) { 264 if (myMCExpr->evaluateAsAbsolute(Res)) {
265 int bits = immBits + zeroBits; 265 int bits = immBits + zeroBits;
266 // Field bit range is zerobits + bits 266 // Field bit range is zerobits + bits
267 // zeroBits must be 0 267 // zeroBits must be 0
268 if (Res & ((1 << zeroBits) - 1)) 268 if (Res & ((1 << zeroBits) - 1))
269 return false; 269 return false;
270 if (isSigned) { 270 if (isSigned) {
271 if (Res < (1LL << (bits - 1)) && Res >= -(1LL << (bits - 1))) 271 if (Res < (1LL << (bits - 1)) && Res >= -(1LL << (bits - 1)))
272 return true; 272 return true;
273 } else { 273 } else {
274 if (bits == 64) 274 if (bits == 64)
275 return true; 275 return true;
276 if (Res >= 0) 276 if (Res >= 0)
277 return ((uint64_t)Res < (uint64_t)(1ULL << bits)); 277 return ((uint64_t)Res < (uint64_t)(1ULL << bits));
278 else { 278 else {
279 const int64_t high_bit_set = 1ULL << 63; 279 const int64_t high_bit_set = 1ULL << 63;
280 const uint64_t mask = (high_bit_set >> (63 - bits)); 280 const uint64_t mask = (high_bit_set >> (63 - bits));
281 return (((uint64_t)Res & mask) == mask); 281 return (((uint64_t)Res & mask) == mask);
282 } 282 }
283 } 283 }
284 } else if (myMCExpr->getKind() == MCExpr::SymbolRef && isRelocatable) 284 } else if (myMCExpr->getKind() == MCExpr::SymbolRef && isRelocatable)
285 return true; 285 return true;
286 else if (myMCExpr->getKind() == MCExpr::Binary || 286 else if (myMCExpr->getKind() == MCExpr::Binary ||
287 myMCExpr->getKind() == MCExpr::Unary) 287 myMCExpr->getKind() == MCExpr::Unary)
288 return true; 288 return true;
289 } 289 }
290 return false; 290 return false;
291 } 291 }
